# Author Kit - Claude Code Instructions

You are an AI writing assistant working within the Author Kit framework.

## Project Structure

- `.authorkit/memory/constitution.md` - Style bible
- `.authorkit/templates/` - Book templates
- `{{SCRIPT_DIR}}` - Automation scripts
- `book/` - Book workspace

## Workflow

Use `/authorkit.*` commands from `{{COMMAND_SOURCE}}` to run the structured workflow:

**Core flow**: constitution -> conceive -> clarify (opt, structured Q&A on concept) -> discuss (opt, open brainstorm) -> research (opt, repeatable) -> world.build (opt) -> outline -> chapters -> chapter.plan -> chapter.draft -> chapter.review -> analyze / revise.

**Foundation commands** (run once, in order):
- `constitution` — voice/tone/style rules; the "style bible" all chapters are written and reviewed against
- `conceive` — create `concept.md` and the `book/` workspace from a natural-language premise
- `clarify` — resolve concept ambiguities through structured Q&A; writes accepted answers into `concept.md`
- `discuss` — open-ended brainstorming; read-only by default
- `research` — ground a topic with web/news/wikipedia/MCP sources; writes reusable notes
- `world.build` — establish characters, places, organizations, history, systems before writing
- `outline` — full or partial book outline with chapter summaries, character arcs, thematic threads
- `chapters` — convert the outline into a chapter-level task list with status markers

**Chapter lifecycle** (per chapter):
- `chapter.plan` — scenes, beats, emotional arc, connections; status `[ ]` -> `[P]`
- `chapter.draft` — write prose; full, scene-by-scene, continue, or single scene; status `[P]` -> `[D]`
- `chapter.help` — targeted help on a specific passage while drafting
- `chapter.review` — review against plan, constitution, characters, world; status `[D]` -> `[X]` or `[R]`
- `chapter.reorder` — move/split/merge/insert/remove chapters with auto-renumbering

**Quality & analysis**:
- `analyze` — cross-chapter consistency and quality (read-only by default; gated drift remediation)
- `revise` — apply targeted fixes from review or analysis

**Mid-process tools** (available anytime once `concept.md` exists):
- `amend` — propagate a direction or fact change across all artifacts
- `park` — defer a creative decision with a deadline; resolve later
- `snapshot` — bookmark current state (git tag + narrative summary) before risky changes
- `whatif` — try a direction on an experimental branch; merge or discard
- `world.sync` — extract new world details from chapters, verify consistency, rebuild the index

## Notes

- Use absolute paths when operating on files.
- World files use YAML frontmatter metadata.
- Rebuild `world/_index.md` with `authorkit.world.sync` after world edits.
- Prefer original, distinctive character/place names; avoid repeated stock name patterns and generic defaults.
- Anchor prose continuity to constitution + `book/style-anchor.md` + the last two approved chapter drafts when available.
- Handoff `prompt:` strings may contain bracketed placeholders such as `[N]` (current chapter), `[N+1]` (next chapter), `[PD-NNN]` (parked decision id), or `[topic]`/`[focus area]`. When forwarding a handoff, substitute the relevant value from the conversation context — never forward the literal bracketed text.
